definitions.definition: A maritime traditional county of Wales . bounded to the north by the Irish Sea , to the east by Denbighshire , to the south by Cardigan Bay and Merionethshire , and to the west by Caernarfon Bay and the Menai Strait , which separates it from Anglesey . The county is now mostly in Gwynedd .
